


# ğŸ” Data De-Identification and Masking Website

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

The Data De-Identification and Masking Website is a privacy-focused application designed to identify and protect sensitive Personal Identifiable Information (PII) in digital documents. The system automatically detects Indian-specific PII such as Aadhaar numbers, PAN cards, credit card numbers, and email addresses, and applies de-identification techniques to ensure data privacy and regulatory compliance.

## ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

Organizations often handle large volumes of sensitive data that must be protected to comply with privacy regulations. Manual identification and masking of PII is time-consuming and error-prone. This project addresses the need for an automated solution to accurately detect and de-identify sensitive information in files.

## ğŸ’¡ Solution Approach

* Developed a web-based application to scan uploaded files
* Used customized regular expressions (regex) to identify Indian PII
* Validated detection accuracy by identifying true and false positives
* Applied anonymization and pseudo-anonymization techniques to mask data
* Provided preview of masked content before downloading
* Generated output files and downloadable reports
* Displayed insights and statistics through a dashboard

## âœ¨ Key Features

* Detection of Indian PII (Aadhaar, PAN, Credit Card, Email)
* File upload and processing
* Secure masking of sensitive data
* Preview masked data before export
* Search and selectively mask specific PII fields
* Download masked files and reports
* Dashboard with data statistics and insights

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

* **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript
* **Backend:** Python / Java / Node.js *(update as per your project)*
